31/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic received a letter Tuesday (30 March) from his US counterpart, George W. 
Bush, expressing Washington's gratitude for Croatia's support in the global fight against terrorism. 
He said that while efforts to help the Iraqis in reconstructing their country and society continue, the world should also focus on the situation in Afghanistan and the war against terrorism as a whole. 
Bush said he was pleased the global coalition had Croatia as partner in the fight against terrorism and repression. 
(HINA - 30/03/04)
